
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-voit-i2rs-pub-sub-requirements-00.txt'>
    <title>"Requirements for Subscription to YANG Datastores", Eric Voit, Alex Clemm, Alberto Prieto</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-voit-i2rs-pub-sub-requirements-00.txt</link>
    <description>This document provides requirements for a service that allows client applications to subscribe to updates of a YANG datastore.  Based on criteria negotiated as part of a subscription, updates will be pushed to targeted recipients.  Such a capability eliminates the need for periodic polling of YANG datastores by applications and fills a functional gap in existing YANG transports (i.e.  Netconf and Restconf).  Such a service can be summarized as a "pub/sub" service for YANG datastore updates.  Beyond a set of basic requirements for the service, various refinements are addressed.  These refinements include: periodicity of object updates, filtering out of objects underneath a requested a subtree, and delivery QoS guarantees.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-12-11T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
